summary_text: 1. I was working on the warehouse floor. 2. I started to feel strange and lightheaded. 3. I felt a tightness and pressure in my chest. 4. The manager saw me and came to help. 5. The manager took me to the staff room to rest. 6. I recovered and learned to take care of myself.

1. I was working on the warehouse floor. 2. I had been feeling a bit strange and lightheaded. 3. I attributed my feeling to hunger and not eating. 4. I started to feel a strange tightness and pressure in my chest. 5. I stopped working and leaned against a nearby wall. 6. The pressure in my chest got stronger and I felt my heart pounding. 7. I started seeing spots and felt sweat dripping down my forehead and arms. 8. I tried to take deep breaths but couldn't catch my breath. 9. My manager saw me and called out to check if I was alright. 10. The manager caught me as I was about to drop to the ground. 11. He took me to the staff room and helped me rest and recover. 12. I later realized I had been having a panic attack.

1. I was at work one day. 2. I was doing my usual job on the warehouse floor. 3. I was stocking boxes and organizing merchandise. 4. I had been working for a few hours. 5. It was getting late. 6. I felt a bit strange and lightheaded. 7. I thought it was due to hunger. 8. I hadn't eaten yet that day. 9. I started to feel tightness and pressure in my chest. 10. I stopped what I was doing. 11. I leaned against a nearby wall. 12. The pressure in my chest got stronger. 13. I could feel my heart pounding. 14. I started seeing spots. 15. Sweat was dripping down my forehead and arms. 16. I tried to take deep breaths. 17. I couldn't catch my breath. 18. I was really scared. 19. I didn't know what to do. 20. I heard the manager's voice. 21. The manager had seen me and called out. 22. Someone had noticed me and was checking on me. 23. I tried to yell back, but couldn't. 24. The manager walked towards me. 25. I felt my world going dark. 26. I started to drop to the ground. 27. The manager caught me before I fell. 28. He took me to the staff room and sat me down. 29. The experience taught me to rest and eat properly.

I stopped what I was doing and leaned against a wall. 11. The pressure in my chest got stronger. 12. I could feel my heart pounding. 13. I started seeing spots. 14. Sweat was dripping down my forehead and arms. 15. I tried to take deep breaths. 16. I couldn't catch my breath. 17. I was really scared. 18. The manager saw me and called out to me. 19. I tried to yell back but couldn't find my voice. 20. The manager caught me as I was falling to the ground. 21. He took me to the staff room and sat me down. 22. I felt better after resting and drinking water.
